# Web accessibility

All code added or changed in this repo must support **WCAG 2.2 Level AA** where applicable (W3C [Understanding WCAG 2.2](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/)).

## Markup and semantics

- Use semantic HTML first: landmarks (`header`, `nav`, `main`, `footer`), headings in order (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`), lists for lists, `button` vs `a href`.
- Provide a **skip link** to `#main-content` when the page has repeated navigation.
- Give every page a unique, accurate `<title>`; keep `lang` on `<html>` correct.
- Do not use `aria-hidden="true"` on content that is the only source of important information; offer an equivalent for assistive tech (e.g. visually hidden list) if visuals are decorative or duplicated.

## Keyboard and focus

- Everything interactive must be reachable and operable with keyboard only; no keyboard traps.
- **Visible focus** for `:focus-visible` (never remove focus outlines without a stronger replacement).
- `tabindex` only when necessary; avoid positive values.

## Images and media

- Meaningful images: descriptive `alt`. Decorative: `alt=""` and hide from AT if needed.
- Video/audio: captions / transcripts when adding media (future).

## Color, contrast, and motion

- Text contrast at least **4.5:1** for normal text, **3:1** for large text; UI components and graphics that convey information need **3:1** against adjacent colors.
- Do not rely on color alone for meaning (e.g. underline links or add text/icons).
- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`**: reduce or disable non-essential animation.
- Test **forced-colors** / high contrast: critical text (e.g. gradient text tricks) must remain readable.

## Links and new windows

- Link purpose clear from text or context; use `aria-label` when visible text is insufficient.
- **`target="_blank"`**: always pair with `rel="noopener noreferrer"` and tell users a new tab/window opens (`aria-label` or visually hidden text), e.g. “(opens in new tab)”.

## Forms (when added)

- Visible labels (or `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby`); associate errors with fields; don’t rely on placeholder alone.

## Dynamic content (when added)

- Announce important updates with live regions or focus management as appropriate.

Prefer manual checks (keyboard, screen reader, zoom to 200%) for this static site; automated tools are supplementary.
